  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Seeking to represent consumer interests in the debate on corporate social responsibility in Brazil, Idec, supported by Oxfam Novib,is developing the third edition of the Responsible Banks Guide (2012-2013).
Previous editions can be found at: www.guiadosbancosresponsaveis.org.br
The second edition of the Brazilian Bankwiser has been launched in October 2012.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="24">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDEC - Instituto Brasileiro de Defe do Consumidor</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDEC, the Brazilian institute for consumer interests, was founded in 1987. It is a civic organisation without profit motives or political preferences, and independent of economic interests. Oxfam Novib has been supporting IDEC since 1998. Some of the results it has achieved in recent years are safer condoms for men, a ban on genetically manipulated foods, withdrawal from the market of more than 100 kinds of antibiotics, legal aid against excessive increases in health insurance premiums, and a substantialreduction of the costs of reconnecting water.
Together with the Dutch Consumer Union Oxfam Novib has also supported an improvement of IDECs services to its members and the public.
Since 2014, IDEC is the lead of the Brazilian coalition of the Fair Finance Guide. Main themes are thetransparancy of the Brazilian banks in international perspective, the integration of ESG criteria in bank policies and practices and the socio-environmental effects of bank credits to specific sectors like agro industry, mining and power generation. The BrazilianFFG gives specific attention to Consumer Protection and Financial Inclusion issues. The website of the Guia dos Bancos Respons&#xE1;veisgive an annual update of the assessment of the sustainability of the banks&apos; policies.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
